Multi branch banking management system

Compilation instructions
- Compiler: Any C++11 compatible compiler (Visual Studio, g++, MinGW)
- Command: g++ main.cpp -o banking.exe
- Note: Works on Windows (uses _mkdir function)

The default teller login
- Teller ID: T001
- Password: admin123
- Branch: Johannesburg Main (Code: 001)

How to use it

Creating the customer accounts (Teller only):
1. Login with teller credentials
2. Select "Register Customer" from teller menu
3. Choose account type (Savings/Cheque/Fixed Deposit/Student)
4. Enter customer details (ID, name, contact, email, address, DOB)
5. Enter initial deposit (minimum depends on account type)
6. System generates Account Number (ACC-001-XXXXX) and 5-digit PIN
7. **WRITE DOWN THE PIN** - displayed only once!

Customer login:
1. Select "Customer Login" from main menu
2. Enter Account Number (ACC-001-10000)
3. Enter 5-digit PIN (from the registration)
4. After 3 failed attempts, account locks temporarily

What you can do:
- Check balance
- Deposit money
- Withdraw money (respects minimum balance)
- Transfer funds between accounts
- View transaction statement (last 10 transactions)
- Change PIN

Reports available (Teller menu)
- Daily Transaction Report
- Customer Account Summary  
- Branch Performance Report
- Inter-Branch Comparison

The File storage
All data saved to binary files:
- customers.dat - Account details (encrypted PINs)
- transactions.dat - Transaction history
- branches.dat - Branch information
- tellers.dat - Teller credentials
- system_config.txt - System settings

Backup and export
